    {
      "id": "950d97a6_69d582fe",
      "file_path": "runtime-controlloop/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/controlloop/runtime/instantiation/ControlLoopInstantiationProvider.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 273,
      "message": "The reason I had to put the Control Loop Name is that the /instantiation/command endpoint receives a PUT request, and the body receives a Control Loop Name and version and not the Definition name and version, this is why I had to apply it differently.\n\nI might suggest change the /instantiation/command endpoint to receive the Tosca Concept Identifier instead of the Control Loop Name and version.  But since we need to get this functionality ready for Istanbul I could open up a ticket to correct this in the Jackarta Release?\n\nBellow is the JSON schema the endpoint receives.\n\n{\n    \"orderedState\": \"UNINITIALISED\",\n    \"controlLoopIdentifierList\": [\n        {\n            \"name\": \"PMSHInstance1\",\n            \"version\": \"1.0.1\"\n        }\n    ]\n}",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7660,
        "name": "Bruno Militzer",
        "display_name": "Bruno Militzer",
        "email": "bruno.militzer@est.tech",
        "username": "brunomilitzer"
      },
      "updated": "2021-08-18 08:52:04.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "e9dca6de_92a32a2c",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "4b4e1541_118c58aa",
      "file_path": "models/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/controlloop/models/messages/rest/instantiation/ControlLoopNameVersion.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 25,
      "message": "ToscaConceptIdentifier is a generic class used wherever we need a name/version pair.  If a \"Control Loop\" is a \"TOSCA concept\", then it's appropriate to remove the \"ControlLoopNameVersion\" class and use ToscaConceptIdentifier instead; we replaced similar structures in policy/models with ToscaConceptIdentifier, several releases back.\n\nIf a \"Control Loop\" is NOT a \"TOSCA concept\", then it makes sense to use a different class.  However, in that case, I would suggest we create a generic NameVersion class in policy/models and use that instead.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-08-18 13:44:46.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9e5393df_1943fd67",
      "unresolved": true
    },
